snippet:
On a Sunday evening, you would expect this prime location to be crowded. It wasn't. My family almost had an entire corner of the outlet to ourselves.
This corner overlooked the Miri-Pujut highway, with decor reminiscent of a ranch house - a quiet cosy corner to chew on succulent chicken. Quiet because of the deafening blasts of rockets and missiles raining down on Lebanon, Israel, Yemen and Gaza.
It's strange how the geopolitics of a region thousands of kilometres away could shorten queues here.
We ruminated over this anomaly because the chicken we were served tasted above average - probably because our digestive juices were in overdrive after a long day...
